reviews.text: The whole dining experience is very poor. Their phone isn't working no matter how many times you call. Food quality is far from authentic Italian food. Undoubtedly the portion is big, for example pasta there will be a big size of pasta, but ingredients can be insufficient and thus not worthwhile.  Both red and white sauce tastes very blend. Meatballs are tasteless and hard. Last time visit

Very disappointing dining experience.  
Not expecting something great like handmade pasta or anything cooked by an Italian chef,  but around $130 per pasta I do expect to have better taste and higher quality/more ingredients on the plate.  The sauce is very plain, ham is slim and few, after a few bites we cannot continue.

Festival walk.  Large comfy location with very big portions which I love.  Price is quite fair and food as well within acceptable.  Only problems I had with this visit was that they totally lacked service.  Wasn't too busy but the probably 7 or 8 servers they had on the floor were all busboys (acted like) and had to ask the floor supervisor to do anything.  I literally had to make room for every single dish that arrived for them as they stood in front of my table and waited.  And lastly, one of the dishes was the whole fish.  If your gonna serve a fish whole, either debone it or let the customer know, menu did not say nor did the server mention.
Large and cozy place. Tasty pizzas and starters are worth trying. Ain't that expensive and would recommend for small groups.
Food is so-so and the portions seem to be smaller than before. We waited for over 45min for dessert.

reviews.text: Good arcade to shop for medium to medium-high end brands in a spacious environment with both restaurants and food court to suit varying tastes of customers. Great parking lot. Multiple sakes receipts accepted for free parking.

Very crowded and very clean like a hospital. Come here on Sunday and you can enjoy waiting for a table for an hour with everyone. Best place if you want to buy a Rolex for $900,000 to go with your yacht sitting in a port in Italy.
Multiple restaurants and shops. A very big mall, and a nice theater to watch movies. The restaurants were also very nice. A very good shopping mall overall.

I like Festival Walk as it is rarely super crowded like the malls at Sha Tin always seem to be. The TASTE supermarket is fantastic here with a range of products from around the world including Waitrose products and a good frozen section. Other stores I like here are Zara Home, Log On, M&S and the Cinema which let's you bring Starbucks in. I sometimes come here to walk around on rainy days too as it is so big and there are very few shoppers with suitcases.

I like Windows shopping here.cause if not people mountain people sea. Can very relaxed to take a look.some shop I used take a look.like hk a female designer. She design Chinese match west.she control color very. Very good. Also one best of world shoe shop. Tecstoni.name may be not correct. It is one of best Italian designer band shoe shop.
